<emphasis id="B937EAC81656FFADFCF5FB2B2EC6158C" bold="true" box="[839,981,1222,1247]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">
<typeStatus id="54F888781656FFADFCF5FB2B2E6C158D" box="[839,895,1223,1247]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Type</typeStatus>
species
</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C434D591656FFADFC51FB2B2887158D" authority="Bacescu et Iliffe, 1986" authorityName="Bacescu et Iliffe" authorityYear="1986" box="[995,1428,1223,1247]" class="Diplopoda" family="Abacionidae" genus="Platyops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Callipodida" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sterreri">
<emphasis id="B937EAC81656FFADFC51FB2B2984158C" box="[995,1175,1223,1247]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Platyops sterreri</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFD24B2B1656FFADFB2DFB2B2887158D" author="Bacescu, M. &amp; T. M. Iliffe" box="[1183,1428,1223,1247]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" pagination="93 - 104" refId="ref35221" refString="Bacescu, M., and T. M. Iliffe. 1986. Bermudamysis g. n., Platyops g. n. and other mysids from Bermudian caves. Stygologia 2 (1 / 2): 93 - 104." type="journal article" year="1986">Băcescu et Iliffe, 1986</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, by monotypy.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C35965511656FFADFCF5FAFD291D16ED" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BFC36DA1656FFADFCF5FAFD280B1746" blockId="44.[839,1467,1297,1556]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">
<emphasis id="B937EAC81656FFADFCF5FAFD2EA6147B" bold="true" box="[839,949,1297,1321]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Telson narrowly trapezoidal (nearly triangular), apically truncated, without cleft, bearing rather long spiniform setae. Eyes with distomedial spine directed forward; eye cornea shifted to lateral side; eyestalk without distolateral lobe. Segment 3 of antennular peduncle with thin distomedial setae, not directed backwards. Pereopod 2 carpopropodus multisegmented. Pereopods 3−6 preischium without process; ischium without flagellated spiniform setae. Uropodal endopod without spiniform setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFC36DA1656FFADFCF5F9C5291D16ED" blockId="44.[839,1467,1577,1983]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">
<emphasis id="B937EAC81656FFADFCF5F9C52EC71713" bold="true" box="[839,980,1577,1601]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Comparison</emphasis>
. The most characteristic feature of this genus is the eye structure, particularly the presence of a strong anterior spine, directed forward. A spine on the eyestalk is found in certain members of 
<taxonomicName id="4C434D591656FFADFBC9F96E29EC17CB" authorityName="Czerniavsky" authorityYear="1882" box="[1147,1279,1666,1689]" class="Malacostraca" family="Mysidae" genus="Heteromysis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mysida" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B937EAC81656FFADFBC9F96E29EC17CB" box="[1147,1279,1666,1689]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Heteromysis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but the direction of the spine is unique. This is the only genus in the tribe, in which the telson cleft is missing. 
<taxonomicName id="4C434D591656FFADFB15F95028171786" authorityName="Bacescu et Iliffe" authorityYear="1986" box="[1191,1284,1724,1748]" class="Diplopoda" family="Abacionidae" genus="Platyops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Callipodida" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B937EAC81656FFADFB15F95028171786" box="[1191,1284,1724,1748]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Platyops</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
does not seem to be particularly close to any other genus of 
<taxonomicName id="4C434D591656FFADFA91F93528AB17A3" authorityName="Norman" authorityYear="1892" box="[1315,1464,1753,1777]" class="Malacostraca" family="Mysidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mysida" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Heteromysini">Heteromysini</taxonomicName>
. At the same time it has all the characters of the tribe: pereopod 1 endopod is differentiated from the pereopod 2 endopod, prehensile (in 
<taxonomicName id="4C434D591656FFADFBF9F8DE29A1161B" authorityName="Daneliya" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Bowman" baseAuthorityYear="1985" box="[1099,1202,1841,1865]" class="Diplopoda" family="Abacionidae" genus="Platyops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Callipodida" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dennisi">
<emphasis id="B937EAC81656FFADFBF9F8DE29A1161B" box="[1099,1202,1841,1865]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">P. dennisi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C434D591656FFADFB5AF8DE2842161B" authorityName="Bacescu et Iliffe" authorityYear="1986" box="[1256,1361,1842,1865]" class="Diplopoda" family="Abacionidae" genus="Platyops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Callipodida" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sterreri">
<emphasis id="B937EAC81656FFADFB5AF8DE2842161B" box="[1256,1361,1842,1865]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">P. sterreri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
[
<bibRefCitation id="EFD24B2B1656FFADFAEDF8DE2ECB1635" author="Bacescu, M. &amp; T. M. Iliffe" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" pagination="93 - 104" refId="ref35221" refString="Bacescu, M., and T. M. Iliffe. 1986. Bermudamysis g. n., Platyops g. n. and other mysids from Bermudian caves. Stygologia 2 (1 / 2): 93 - 104." type="journal article" year="1986">Băcescu et Iliffe, 1986</bibRefCitation>
]), with 2-segmented carpopropodus (uniquely 3-segmented only in 
<taxonomicName id="4C434D591656FFADFB83F88129B816D6" authorityName="Daneliya" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Hanamura et Kase" baseAuthorityYear="2004" box="[1073,1195,1901,1924]" class="Diplopoda" family="Abacionidae" genus="Platyops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Callipodida" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stenoura" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis id="B937EAC81656FFADFB83F88129B816D6" box="[1073,1195,1901,1924]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">P. stenoura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A20457B31656FFADFB07F880282216D6" box="[1205,1329,1900,1924]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, see below), pereopod 2 endopod is differentiated from pereopods 3−6, and other features.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C35965511657FFACFFCBFF742FFE13E0" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BFC36DA1657FFACFFCBFF742F61135D" blockId="45.[121,749,151,527]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">
<emphasis id="B937EAC81657FFACFFCBFF742DF211E2" bold="true" box="[121,225,152,176]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD24B2B1657FFACFF5DFF742CFE11FD" author="Bacescu, M. &amp; T. M. Iliffe" box="[239,493,151,176]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" pagination="93 - 104" refId="ref35221" refString="Bacescu, M., and T. M. Iliffe. 1986. Bermudamysis g. n., Platyops g. n. and other mysids from Bermudian caves. Stygologia 2 (1 / 2): 93 - 104." type="journal article" year="1986">Băcescu &amp; Iliffe (1986)</bibRefCitation>
remarked that 
<taxonomicName id="4C434D591657FFACFD3DFF7B2FFF11FD" authorityName="Bacescu et Iliffe" authorityYear="1986" box="[655,748,151,175]" class="Diplopoda" family="Abacionidae" genus="Platyops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Callipodida" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B937EAC81657FFACFD3DFF7B2FFF11FD" box="[655,748,151,175]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Platyops</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was convergent with 
<taxonomicName id="4C434D591657FFACFEEDFF592F19119F" authorityName="Bacescu" authorityYear="1968" box="[351,522,181,205]" class="Malacostraca" family="Mysidae" genus="Heteromysoides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mysida" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B937EAC81657FFACFEEDFF592F19119F" box="[351,522,181,205]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Heteromysoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which was indeed a manifestation that the genus is related to the heteromysine genera. Original placement of 
<taxonomicName id="4C434D591657FFACFE0FFF032F091055" authorityName="Bacescu et Iliffe" authorityYear="1986" box="[445,538,239,263]" class="Diplopoda" family="Abacionidae" genus="Platyops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Callipodida" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B937EAC81657FFACFE0FFF032F091055" box="[445,538,239,263]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Platyops</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<taxonomicName id="4C434D591657FFACFD8EFF032F9B1055" box="[572,648,239,263]" class="Malacostraca" family="Mysidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mysida" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Mysini">Mysini</taxonomicName>
caused it to be missing among the heteromysine genera in subsequent works, before 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD24B2B1657FFACFEA1FEC62CFE1010" author="Nouvel, H. &amp; J. P. Casanova &amp; J. P. Lagardere" box="[275,493,298,322]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" pagination="39 - 86" refId="ref38910" refString="Nouvel, H., J. P. Casanova, and J. P. Lagardere. 1999. Ordre des Mysidaces. Memoires de l'Institut Oceanographique, Monaco 19: 39 - 86." type="journal article" year="1999">
Nouvel 
<emphasis id="B937EAC81657FFACFEDBFEC72C8B1010" box="[361,408,298,322]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">et al</emphasis>
. (1999)
</bibRefCitation>
finally placed in within 
<taxonomicName id="4C434D591657FFACFFCBFEAB2C1D100D" authorityName="Norman" authorityYear="1892" box="[121,270,327,351]" class="Malacostraca" family="Mysidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mysida" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Heteromysini">Heteromysini</taxonomicName>
. Probably by a mistake it was mentioned as a part of the subfamily 
<taxonomicName id="4C434D591657FFACFEE0FE892CF5102F" box="[338,486,357,381]" class="Malacostraca" family="Mysidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mysida" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Leptomysinae">Leptomysinae</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFD24B2B1657FFACFE40FE892DA010C8" author="San Vicente, C. &amp; F. Monniot" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" pagination="323 - 346" refId="ref39620" refString="San Vicente, C., and F. Monniot. 2014. The ascidian-associated mysid Corellamysis eltanina gen. nov., sp. nov. (Mysida, Mysidae, Heteromysinae): a new symbiotic relationship from the Southern Ocean. Zootaxa 3780 (2): 323 - 346. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3780.2.6" type="journal article" year="2014">
<collectingCountry id="F354764A1657FFACFE40FE892F7C102F" box="[498,623,357,381]" name="Saint Vincent and the Grenadines" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">San Vicente</collectingCountry>
&amp; Monniot, 2014
</bibRefCitation>
). However, because of the weekly prehensile nature of pereopod 1 endopod in the 
<typeStatus id="54F888781657FFACFE27FE4C2CD010EA" box="[405,451,416,440]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">type</typeStatus>
species, it found its position in the heteromysine tribe 
<taxonomicName id="4C434D591657FFACFECCFE512FF91087" authority="(Wittmann et al., 2014)" baseAuthorityName="Wittmann" baseAuthorityYear="2014" box="[382,746,445,469]" class="Malacostraca" family="Mysidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mysida" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Mysidetini">
Mysidetini (
<bibRefCitation id="EFD24B2B1657FFACFE49FE512FF21087" author="Wittmann, K. J. &amp; A. P. Ariani &amp; J. - P. Lagardere" box="[507,737,445,469]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" pagination="404 - 406" refId="ref41468" refString="Wittmann, K. J., A. P. Ariani, and J. - P. Lagardere. 2014. Orders Lophogastrida Boas, 1883, Stygiomysida Tchindonova, 1981, and Mysida Boas, 1883 (also known collectively as Mysidacea), pp. 189 - 396, 404 - 406. In Treatise on Zoology - Anatomy, Taxonomy, Biology. The Crustacea. Revised and updated, as well as extended from the Traite de Zoologie, ed. J. C. von Vaupel Klein, M. Charmantier-Daures, and F. R. Schram, vol. 4, part B (54). https: // doi. org / 10.1163 / 9789004264939 _ 006" type="book chapter" year="2014">
Wittmann 
<emphasis id="B937EAC81657FFACFDD8FE522F841087" box="[618,663,445,469]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">et al</emphasis>
., 2014
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. With the renewed concept of 
<taxonomicName id="4C434D591657FFACFE18FE362F2D10A0" authorityName="Norman" authorityYear="1892" box="[426,574,474,498]" class="Malacostraca" family="Mysidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mysida" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Heteromysini">Heteromysini</taxonomicName>
, I revise here the position of 
<taxonomicName id="4C434D591657FFACFF40FE1B2C5C135D" authorityName="Bacescu et Iliffe" authorityYear="1986" box="[242,335,503,527]" class="Diplopoda" family="Abacionidae" genus="Platyops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Callipodida" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B937EAC81657FFACFF40FE1B2C5C135D" box="[242,335,503,527]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Platyops</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and transfer it to this tribe.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFC36DA1657FFACFFCBFDC92FFE13E0" blockId="45.[121,749,549,690]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">
<emphasis id="B937EAC81657FFACFFCBFDC92C1F136F" bold="true" box="[121,268,549,573]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Composition</emphasis>
. Three species are included into 
<taxonomicName id="4C434D591657FFACFD34FDC92FF6136F" authorityName="Bacescu et Iliffe" authorityYear="1986" box="[646,741,549,573]" class="Diplopoda" family="Abacionidae" genus="Platyops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Callipodida" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B937EAC81657FFACFD34FDC92FF6136F" box="[646,741,549,573]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Platyops</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: 
<taxonomicName id="4C434D591657FFACFFCBFDAE2CE71308" authority="(Bowman, 1985)" authorityName="Daneliya" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Bowman" baseAuthorityYear="1985" box="[121,500,578,602]" class="Diplopoda" family="Abacionidae" genus="Platyops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Callipodida" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dennisi" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis id="B937EAC81657FFACFFCBFDAE2C231308" box="[121,304,578,602]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Platyops dennisi</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFD24B2B1657FFACFEF3FDAE2CFF1308" author="Bowman, T. E." box="[321,492,578,602]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" pagination="945 - 948" refId="ref35524" refString="Bowman, T. E. 1985. Heteromysoides dennisi, a new mysidacean crustacean from Cemetery Cave, Grand Bahama Island. Proceedings of the Biological Society of Washington 98 (4): 945 - 948." type="journal article" year="1985">Bowman, 1985</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B937EAC81657FFACFE4CFDAE2F6E1308" bold="true" box="[510,637,578,602]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A20457B31657FFACFE4CFDAE2F6E1308" box="[510,637,578,602]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C434D591657FFACFD3CFDAE2CE5132A" authority="(Hanamura et Kase, 2001)" authorityName="Daneliya" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Hanamura et Kase" baseAuthorityYear="2001" class="Diplopoda" family="Abacionidae" genus="Platyops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Callipodida" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="simplex" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis id="B937EAC81657FFACFD3CFDAE2DD91325" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Platyops simplex</emphasis>
(Hanamura et Kase, 2001)
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B937EAC81657FFACFDB2FD8C2F6E132A" bold="true" box="[512,637,608,632]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A20457B31657FFACFDB2FD8C2F6E132A" box="[512,637,608,632]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
(formerly 
<taxonomicName id="4C434D591657FFACFFCBFD912C3613C7" authorityName="Bacescu" authorityYear="1968" box="[121,293,637,661]" class="Malacostraca" family="Mysidae" genus="Heteromysoides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mysida" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B937EAC81657FFACFFCBFD912C3613C7" box="[121,293,637,661]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Heteromysoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), 
<taxonomicName id="4C434D591657FFACFE8DFD912DA513E0" authority="(Hanamura et Kase, 2004)" authorityName="Daneliya" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Hanamura et Kase" baseAuthorityYear="2004" class="Diplopoda" family="Abacionidae" genus="Platyops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Callipodida" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stenoura" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis id="B937EAC81657FFACFE8DFD912F1613C7" box="[319,517,637,661]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Platyops stenoura</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFD24B2B1657FFACFDA5FD912DBC13E0" author="Hanamura, Y. &amp; T. Kase" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" pagination="2145 - 2152" refId="ref36833" refString="Hanamura, Y., and T. Kase. 2004. Heteromysoides (Crustacea: Mysidacea: Heteromysini) from a submarine cave on Grand Cayman, the Caribbean Sea: descriptions of a new and a rare species. Journal of Natural History 38 (17): 2145 - 2152. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222930310001625914" type="journal article" year="2004">Hanamura et Kase, 2004</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B937EAC81657FFACFF09FD762C2113E0" bold="true" box="[187,306,666,690]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A20457B31657FFACFF09FD762C2113E0" box="[187,306,666,690]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
(formerly 
<taxonomicName id="4C434D591657FFACFE12FD762F5B13E0" authorityName="Bacescu" authorityYear="1968" box="[416,584,666,690]" class="Malacostraca" family="Mysidae" genus="Heteromysoides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mysida" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
